esqlQuery.esql:
// Alert when daemonset available/desired replica ratio drops below 1.
//
// What triggers this alert:
// AVG(available) / AVG(desired) < 1 means some pods are unavailable.
//
// What it means:
// Daemonset not running on all expected nodes — reduced coverage.
//
// Common causes:
// Node scheduling issues, resource constraints, image pull errors, taints.
//
// Handles division by zero: filters out daemonsets with zero desired replicas.
TS metrics-kubernetes.state_daemonset-*
| WHERE `kubernetes.daemonset.replicas.available` IS NOT NULL
| STATS
    avg_available = AVG(`kubernetes.daemonset.replicas.available`),
    avg_desired = AVG(`kubernetes.daemonset.replicas.desired`)
  BY `orchestrator.cluster.name`, `kubernetes.daemonset.name`, `kubernetes.namespace`
| WHERE avg_desired IS NOT NULL AND avg_desired > 0
| EVAL availability_ratio = avg_available / avg_desired
| WHERE availability_ratio < 1
